arch:property.oc:show_val: Phase XII: Robbing and abandonment continue.
Phase XI: Further collapse post-CE 5th c. Possibly the result of the earthquake of CE 512.
Later accumulation of debris after the initial architectural collapse.
Phase XIII: Major collapses continue into the Islamic period.

Locus 1 is a thick layer of soil (Munsell 7.5YR 4/4, Brown) with an even, heavy distribution of materials such as roof tiles and tesserae (One single day, 19.VI.00, saw the removal of 598 roof tile fragments and 145 tesserae). This locus represents later accumulation that washed down for a long period of time from the Lower Temenos and possibly other areas of the temple complex. A large number of elephant capital fragments were found in this locus.
